video.title: Miss Fisher's Murder Mysteries
video.synopsis: Get ready to immerse yourself in the opulent, exciting and sometimes dangerous world of Australia's leading lady, Det. Phryne Fisher.

episodes.synopsis: Returning to Melbourne after years abroad, Phryne Fisher is immediately embroiled in mystery: poisoned husbands, cocaine and smuggling rings.
episodes.title: Cocaine Blues

episodes.synopsis: Phryne decides to travel to the country by train to collect her new motorcar. But the charm of rail travel evaporates when she has to use her pistol.
episodes.title: Murder On The Ballarat Train

episodes.synopsis: Phryne had thought she would dance the night away at the hottest dance hall in town, the Green Mill. That was before death spoiled the evening.
episodes.title: The Green Mill Murder

episodes.synopsis: A young man with a blue tattoo lies cradled in Phryne's arms. Sadly, it's not another scene of glorious seduction. This time it's murder.
episodes.title: Death at Victoria Dock

episodes.synopsis: When a young man is found dead at the Eastern Market, Phryne is plunged into the diverse worlds of Jewish politics, alchemy and poison.
episodes.title: Raisins and Almonds

episodes.synopsis: At a gala performance of "Ruddigore," Phryne meets the gorgeous Lin Chung, who has rescued the theatre's leading man from some thugs in a dark alley.
episodes.title: Ruddy Gore

episodes.synopsis: Ten years after Phryne posed for a famous artist in Paris, his widow arrives in Melbourne asking for her late husband's paintings.
episodes.title: Murder in Montparnasse

episodes.synopsis: Phryne investigates the death of a magazine columnist. To get to the truth, she must unearth the deceptions and rivalries of the magazine's staff.
episodes.title: Away with the Fairies

episodes.synopsis: When a girl whom Phryne had been instructing in etiquette turns up dead, the detective begins to question the worth of table manners and dancing.
episodes.title: Queen of the Flowers

episodes.synopsis: Phryne investigates the death of a female worker in a factory "accident" and  learns that the woman's death might not be the misadventure it seems.
episodes.title: Death by Miss Adventure

episodes.synopsis: Innocent fun turns to horror when one of the sideshow acts in a carnival is murdered. Phryne poses as the magician's assistant, Fern, to investigate.
episodes.title: Blood and Circuses

episodes.synopsis: Phryne's cousins and Aunt Prudence's household come under suspicion when a young girl is found drowned in her aunt's fountain on the eve of a party.
episodes.title: Murder in the Dark

episodes.synopsis: In investigating a murder, Phryne discovers the leading suspect's involvement in a bizarre reincarnation cult, inspired by ancient Egypt.
episodes.title: King Memses' Curse

episodes.synopsis: Phryne disobeys Jack's orders and goes undercover as a fan dancer to investigate a murder involving Jack's former father-in-law.
episodes.title: Murder Most Scandalous

episodes.synopsis: With Aunt Prudence swept up in the new spiritualist fad, Phryne becomes embroiled in a murder committed 10 years prior on the battlefield.
episodes.title: Death Comes Knocking

episodes.synopsis: It's off to the seaside for Phryne and her friends. But their holiday goes awry when burglary, murder and buried treasure are thrown into the mix.
episodes.title: Dead Man's Chest

episodes.synopsis: Phryne is embroiled in the dangerous world of fight-rigging and tribal payback when a gang leader is murdered outside a traveling boxing tent.
episodes.title: Deadweight

episodes.synopsis: The world of high fashion turns deadly when Phryne goes to an exclusive salon for a fitting, only to discover that a prominent lady has been killed.
episodes.title: Murder a la Mode

episodes.synopsis: Good sportsmanship is scarce when Phryne finds the competitive captain of an Australian Rules football team hanging by a rival team's scarf.
episodes.title: Marked for Murder

episodes.synopsis: When a female race car driver is found dead in her roadster, Phryne struggles to convince Jack that her death was no accident.
episodes.title: Blood at the Wheel

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Mac implores an estranged Jack and Phryne to work together to solve a professor's murder. In the process, they find a valuable stolen manuscript.
episodes.title: The Blood of Juana the Mad

episodes.synopsis: Phryne wades into the world of showbiz when a silent movie that's being produced by one of her oldest friends is derailed by murder.
episodes.title: Framed for Murder

episodes.synopsis: Phryne investigates two suspicious deaths at an idyllic vineyard, where murder and hostile townsfolk combine to produce an especially thorny case.
episodes.title: Death on the Vine

episodes.synopsis: The Fisher household's new wireless broadcasts bad news with an on-air murder, prompting Phryne and an undercover Jack to battle a wily killer.
episodes.title: Dead Air

episodes.synopsis: The death of a teenager escaping from a halfway house for wayward girls touches Phryne deeply as her investigation leads to corruption in high places.
episodes.title: Unnatural Habits

episodes.synopsis: While holidaying with Aunt Prudence at a snowbound chalet, Phryne and her friends rush to solve a murder before they become the next victims.
episodes.title: Murder Under the Mistletoe
